     
               <td>
                <p style="font-size: 25px;">
                 Virat Kohli is oneof the most accomplished and celebrated cricketers in the world, particularly renowned for his incredible batting prowess and leadership skills. 
                </p>
 
                <p style="font-size: 25px;">
                <b> Full Name:</b>  Virat Kohli <br>
 <b>Date of Birth:</b> November 5, 1988
 <b>Place of Birth :</b>  Delhi, India
 <b>Nationality: </b> Indian <br>
 <b> Role: </b> Right-handed batsman   <br>
 <b>Teams : </b> India, Royal Challengers Bangalore (Indian Premier League
                </p> 
 
                
                <h2>Early Life:</h2> 
                <p style="font-size: 25px;">
                 Virat Kohli was born into a middle-class Punjabi family. His father, Prem Kohli, worked as a criminal lawyer, and his mother, Saroj Kohli, is a housewife. Kohli showed an early interest in cricket, and his talent was evident from a young age.
                </p> 
                
 
                 <h2>
                     Domestic and Youth Career:
                 </h2> 
                 <p style="font-size: 25px;">
                 Virat Kohli's journey to cricket stardom began in the Delhi youth teams. His consistent performances in age-group cricket and the Ranji Trophy earned him recognition. He captained the India Under-19 team to victory in the 2008 Under-19 World Cup, showcasing his leadership skills.
                </p> 
 
                
                 <h2>International Debut:</h2>  
                 <p style="font-size: 25px;">
                 Kohli made his international debut for India in August 2008 during an ODI against Sri Lanka. His Test debut followed in 2011 against West Indies. Kohli quickly established himself as a key player in the Indian cricket team.
                </p>
 
